The PNGs are ending up to be super large. 12-14 MBs each. The website has trouble loading them. Runnig the command below
seems to have lowered all of them to 3-4 MBs each. This is black magic to me and I have no clue how it did this. But now,
the pizzas should load quicker. :-)
nix-shell -p imagemagick --run "mogrify -resize 50% *.png"
